{"word":"ἀποτρόπαιος","slug":"ἀποτρόπαιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀποτρόπαιος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀποτρέπω'><el>ἀποτρέπω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>averting evil</i>, of Apollo, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>averruncus</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>that ought to be averted, ill-omened</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}